<ns2967:section xmlns:ns2967="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2ee.ejb.transactions.isolation.settingIsolationLevels">

  <ns2968:title xmlns:ns2968="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Setting EJB Isolation Levels</ns2968:title>
  <ns2969:para xmlns:ns2969="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    The EJB and JTA specifications don't specify a standard API for managing the isolation level of
    a resource, <ns2970:abbrev xmlns:ns2970="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">i.e.</ns2970:abbrev> the degree to which the access
    to the resource by one transaction is isolated from other transactions. The setting of the
    isolation level will thus be resource manager specific.
  </ns2969:para>
</ns2967:section>